Functions:

Block of code which performs a specific task

syntax:

def functionName():
    body...


functionName()

..................................

Parameters - variables given in the function declaration

def function(a,b)------here a,b are the parameters


function(1,2) ----- here 1,2 are the arguments

Argument - values given in the time of funtion call!

.....................................

No of Para = No of Arguments in general!!

but if u are not sure about this,, then u can use Arbitrary Arguments
and Arbitrary Keyword Arguemnts...

Arbitrary Arguments and Arbitrary Keyword Arguments allows you to take
multiple argument into a function

Arbitrary Arugents uses only * star
Arbitrary Keyword Arguments uses ** stars

at last
Default Parameter Arguments - these are passed when u are declaring a
function as a default values or argument given to the parameter
soo if the user forgets to give the arguments then these default
parameter arguments are used b y default and the job is done


this way we completed Functions Concept! in python!!



